  "text": "## Firefox DOM Event Dispatch System - Complete Chain\n\nThe Firefox event dispatch system in C++ implements the DOM event specification with a carefully orchestrated flow:\n\n### 1. Event Creation (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:869-1200)\n\nWhen `EventDispatcher::Dispatch()` is called with a `WidgetEvent*` and an `EventTarget*`, it:\n- Validates the event is not already being dispatched (line 878)\n- Creates or uses a provided `dom::Event` object (lines 976-1040)\n- Sets the event target and original target (lines 1019-1039)\n- Creates a temporary DOM event wrapper if needed\n- Initializes `EventChainPreVisitor` with the event details (lines 1060-1061)\n\nThe `CreateEvent()` function (lines 1419-1485) maps internal widget event classes to appropriate DOM event types (UIEvent, KeyboardEvent, MouseEvent, TouchEvent, etc.) based on `aEvent->mClass`.\n\n### 2. Event Target Chain Creation (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:1008-1178)\n\nThe event target chain is built by iterating through the DOM tree hierarchy:\n\n**Initial Target Chain Item Creation (line 1009):**\n- `EventTargetChainItem::Create()` creates the first item from the dispatch target\n- Each item calls `GetEventTargetParent()` to obtain its parent (line 1063)\n\n**Parent Chain Building (lines 1113-1178):**\n- While loop in `EventDispatcher::Dispatch()` creates parent items\n- Each parent is obtained through `GetEventTargetParent()` which uses `mParentTarget` (line 1114)\n- Chain includes all ancestors up to the document root\n- Handles retargeting for shadow DOM boundaries (lines 1127-1137)\n\n**Chain Item Flags (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:383-427):**\n- Each `EventTargetChainItem` stores flags like `mForceContentDispatch`, `mWantsWillHandleEvent`, `mMayHaveManager`\n- These flags are set during `GetEventTargetParent()` to optimize dispatch (line 442)\n\n### 3. Capture Phase (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:516-585)\n\nHandled in `EventTargetChainItem::HandleEventTargetChain()`:\n\n**Phase Setup (lines 517-519):**\n```cpp\naVisitor.mEvent->mFlags.mInCapturePhase = true;\naVisitor.mEvent->mFlags.mInBubblingPhase = false;\naVisitor.mEvent->mFlags.mInTargetPhase = false;\n```\n\n**Iteration (lines 520-541):**\n- Iterates backward from the root to the target: `for (uint32_t i = chainLength - 1; i > firstCanHandleEventTargetIdx; --i)`\n- Calls `item.HandleEvent()` for each item in the chain (line 528)\n- Handles event retargeting at anonymous boundaries (lines 531-541)\n- Handles relatedTarget retargeting (lines 549-565)\n\n### 4. Target Phase (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:587-611)\n\n**Target Item Handling:**\n- Sets `mInTargetPhase = true` (line 588)\n- Calls `HandleEvent()` twice: once in capture mode, then again in bubble mode (lines 598, 605)\n- This allows listeners with `capture:true` and `capture:false` to both fire on the target element\n- Handles `PostHandleEvent` for system group (line 609)\n\n### 5. Bubble Phase (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:613-648)\n\n**Phase Setup (lines 600-601):**\n```cpp\naVisitor.mEvent->mFlags.mInCapturePhase = false;\naVisitor.mEvent->mFlags.mInBubblingPhase = true;\n```\n\n**Iteration (lines 614-647):**\n- Iterates forward from target's parent to root\n- Only processes items if `mBubbles` flag is set or event needs retargeting (line 638)\n- Calls `HandleEvent()` for bubbling listeners (line 642)\n\n### 6. Event Listener Invocation (dom/events/EventListenerManager.cpp:1439-1534)\n\n**Main Entry Point - HandleEventInternal():**\n- Sets up context for listener execution (lines 1460-1467)\n- Finds listeners for the event type atom (lines 1481-1517)\n- Handles both \"all events\" listeners and type-specific listeners\n\n**Listener Array Processing - HandleEventWithListenerArray() (lines 1536-1627):**\n- Lazily creates DOM event if needed (lines 1540-1551)\n- Iterates through listeners matching the event phase (lines 1558-1593)\n- For each listener:\n  - Checks phase matching: `listener->MatchesEventPhase(aEvent)` (line 1567)\n  - Validates event trustedness (line 1568)\n  - Handles \"once\" listeners by moving them before invocation (lines 1573-1580)\n\n**Single Listener Invocation - HandleEventSingleListener() (lines 1233-1295):**\n- Sets `aEvent->mCurrentTarget` to the current target (lines 1236-1240)\n- Sets passive listener flag (line 1243)\n- For WebIDL callbacks: calls `callback->HandleEvent(aCurrentTarget, *aDOMEvent, rv)` (lines 1276-1277)\n- For XPCOM callbacks: calls `callback->HandleEvent(aDOMEvent)` (line 1282)\n- Sets exception flag if listener throws (line 1291)\n- Returns whether propagation should continue (line 1294)\n\n### 7. Default Action Execution (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:446-489)\n\n**Activation Behavior Chain Item Methods:**\n\n**LegacyPreActivationBehavior() (lines 446-453):**\n- Called before listeners on elements that want activation behavior\n- Allows elements to suppress default behavior or modify event state\n\n**ActivationBehavior() (lines 466-472):**\n- Called after event listeners have been invoked (in system event group)\n- For HTMLButtonElement (HTMLButtonElement.cpp:315-349): submits form if in form\n- For HTMLInputElement (HTMLInputElement.cpp): varies by input type (checkbox toggles, radio selects, submit/reset submits)\n- Copies `mItemFlags` and `mItemData` to visitor for element-specific processing\n\n**PostHandleEvent() (lines 483-489):**\n- Final post-processing for each chain item\n- Allows elements to clean up or perform final actions\n\n### 8. System Event Group Dispatch (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:651-693)\n\n**System Group Handling:**\n- First dispatches to default event group (content listeners)\n- If event allows system group (line 652), resets propagation flags and retargets\n- Calls callback if provided (line 671) - allows PresShell to handle default actions\n- Re-runs entire dispatch chain for system group listeners\n- System group is protected from content script interference\n\n### 9. Integration Points\n\n**PresShell Integration (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:9099-9101):**\n- `PresShell::EventHandler::DispatchEvent()` bridges between widget system and DOM\n- Converts native widget events to DOM events\n- Provides default action handling through `EventDispatchingCallback`\n\n**Widget Events (widget/BasicEvents.h:637-875):**\n- Core `WidgetEvent` class with message type, flags, and target information\n- Flags control dispatch behavior: `mBubbles`, `mCancelable`, `mInCapturePhase`, etc.\n- Methods: `DefaultPrevented()`, `PreventDefault()`, `StopPropagation()`\n\n**Event Messages (widget/EventMessageList.h):**\n- Defines all event types: eMouseClick, eTouchStart, eKeyDown, etc.\n- Organized by event class and category\n\n### Complete Event Lifecycle Summary\n\n1. **Creation**: WidgetEvent created with message type and target\n2. **DOM Event Wrapper**: Created on demand from WidgetEvent\n3. **Chain Building**: Walk DOM tree from target to root via GetEventTargetParent()\n4. **Capture Phase**: Dispatch from root to target, capture listeners only\n5. **Target Phase**: Dispatch to target element, both capture and bubble listeners\n6. **Bubble Phase**: Dispatch from target parent to root, bubble listeners only\n7. **System Group**: Repeat phases 4-6 for system listeners after default group\n8. **Activation Behavior**: Execute default action (form submission, checkbox toggle, etc.)\n9. **Post-Processing**: Element-specific cleanup via PostHandleEvent()\n\nThis architecture ensures complete separation between content and system events, proper event phase handling, shadow DOM support with retargeting, and clean default action execution following the DOM specification."
